 - [ ] 200 response body has `user.id`, `user.email`, `user.role`, `user.studentVerified`.
 - [ ] 200 response body does NOT contain `passwordHash`, `googleId`, or `emailVerifyTokenHash`.
 
+
+## 13. Student vs manager verification (added with manager-claim system)
+
+Student verification stays Google-only with `@ucdavis.edu`. Manager verification is property-by-property via claim submission + admin approval.
+
+### 13a. Student auto-post
+- [ ] Set `AUTO_APPROVE_VERIFIED_STUDENT_SUBLEASES=true` on Railway.
+- [ ] As a verified UC Davis student, POST /api/subleases with valid body → 201 with `autoApproved: true` and `sublease.moderation === 'approved'`.
+- [ ] Confirm the sublease is immediately visible on `/subleases`.
+
+### 13b. Unverified user blocked
+- [ ] As a non-Davis Google user OR email/password user, POST /api/subleases → 403.
+- [ ] Same applies even with `AUTO_APPROVE_VERIFIED_STUDENT_SUBLEASES=true` — auto-approval only kicks in for *verified* students.
+
+## 14. Manager claim submission
+
+### 14a. High-confidence claim
+- [ ] Sign in as a manager (email/password is fine — managers don't need Google).
+- [ ] Go to `/manager/claim-property?listing=<id>` (or use the dashboard button).
+- [ ] Fill in: workEmail with the property's domain, companyWebsite with same domain.
+- [ ] Submit → 201, response shows `claim.confidence === 'high'`, `claim.status === 'pending'`.
+- [ ] Listing's public page now shows "Claim pending review" badge.
+
+### 14b. Low-confidence claim
+- [ ] Repeat with `workEmail: someone@gmail.com` and any website.
+- [ ] 201, confidence === 'low', status === 'pending'.
+- [ ] Confirm: high confidence does NOT auto-approve. Both end up pending.
+
+### 14c. Re-claim guards
+- [ ] Submit the same claim twice from the same manager → 2nd attempt gets 409.
+- [ ] If listing is already approved-claimed by manager A, manager B's submission → 409.
+
+### 14d. Student blocked
+- [ ] As a logged-in student, POST /api/manager-claims → 403 ("Manager account required").
+
+## 15. Admin claim review
+
+- [ ] As admin, GET /api/admin/manager-claims?status=pending → returns the claim with `confidence`, `emailDomain`, `websiteDomain`, populated `manager` and `listing`.
+- [ ] PATCH /api/admin/manager-claims/:id/approve → 200, listing now `claimedByManager: true`, `claimStatus: 'claimed'`, `managerVerified: true` (because confidence was ≥ medium).
+- [ ] Manager's `verifiedManagerFor` now contains the listing id (verify via /auth/me).
+- [ ] On reload, manager dashboard `/manager` shows the listing under "Your verified properties."
+
+## 16. Claimed-listing edits
+
+Test with `MANAGER_AUTO_APPROVE_CLAIMED_LISTING_UPDATES=true` on Railway.
+
+### 16a. Manager edits own listing
+- [ ] PATCH /api/listings/:id with `{ description, contactEmail, priceMin }` → 200, `autoApproved: true`, `editedFields: ['description', 'contactEmail', 'priceMin']`.
+- [ ] Public listing page reflects the changes immediately.
+- [ ] Listing's `lastManagerUpdateAt` is recent.
+
+### 16b. Manager edits unclaimed listing → 403
+- [ ] PATCH /api/listings/<some-other-listing-id> → 403 with "verified manager claim" message.
+
+### 16c. Dangerous fields silently dropped
+- [ ] PATCH /api/listings/:id with `{ description, verificationStatus, claimedBy, sourceType, manager }`.
+- [ ] Response: `editedFields: ['description']` only. Other fields are ignored — no error, no mutation.
+
+### 16d. Disable auto-approve
+- [ ] Set `MANAGER_AUTO_APPROVE_CLAIMED_LISTING_UPDATES=false` and redeploy.
+- [ ] PATCH /api/listings/:id → 503 with explanatory message.
+
+## 17. Public badges
+
+- [ ] On a verified-claimed listing, the public page shows **"Verified Property Manager"**.
+- [ ] On an approved-but-low-confidence claim, the page shows **"Claimed by Property"**.
+- [ ] On a listing with a pending claim, the page shows **"Claim pending review"**.
+- [ ] On an unclaimed listing, the page shows **"Unclaimed listing"**.
+- [ ] On an `external_import` listing that's never been claimed, the page shows **"External listing — not verified by hone"**.
+
+## 18. Admin claim revocation
+
+- [ ] POST /api/admin/listings/:id/revoke-claim with `{ reason: 'X' }` → 200, listing back to unclaimed.
+- [ ] Manager's `verifiedManagerFor` no longer contains the listing id (verify via fresh /auth/me).
+- [ ] Manager's next PATCH attempt on that listing → 403.
+- [ ] The ManagerClaim record's status is `revoked` with the reason saved as `adminNote`.
+
+## 19. Safety rules (cross-cutting)
+
+- [ ] Manager cannot DELETE student subleases (`DELETE /api/subleases/:id` from manager token whose role !== 'admin' → 403).
+- [ ] Manager cannot PATCH `verificationStatus` on a listing (allowlist drops the field).
+- [ ] Manager cannot remove a student review via the public API (no manager endpoint for this; only admin's `/admin/reviews/:id/remove`).
+- [ ] Manager cannot approve external/Apify leads (no manager endpoint; admin only).
+- [ ] Admin's `/admin/manager-updates` shows recent manager edits, sorted by `lastManagerUpdateAt`.
+
+## 20. Smoke test summary (extended)
+
+```bash
+cd backend
+npm install
+PORT=0 npm test                 # full integration suite (needs Mongo binary)
+node --test test/domainConfidence.test.js test/managerClaim.test.js   # sandbox-runnable unit tests
+
+cd ../frontend
+npm install
+npm run build
+```
